Deprecating GLU:

./c_lib/compat_gl.h:26:        #include <OpenGL/glu.h>
./c_lib/camera/camera.cpp:159:    gluPerspective( fov, ratio, z_near, z_far);
./c_lib/camera/camera.cpp:182:    gluLookAt(x,y,z,
./c_lib/camera/camera.cpp:223:    gluOrtho2D(0, x_size, 0, y_size);
./c_lib/particles/billboard_text.cpp:234:    GLint res = gluProject(x,y,z, model_view_matrix_dbl, projection_matrix, viewport, &sx, &sy, &sz);

<graphitemaster> the gluOrtho2D can be replaced with glOrtho
<graphitemaster> gluProject can be replaced with glLoadMatrix
<graphitemaster> gluLookAt is redundant and so is gluPerspective those two can be removed and replaced with a single glFrustum() call
